{
  "name": "@snowluma/protocol",
  "version": "1.9.9",
  "private": true,
  "type": "module",
  "description": "SnowLuma protocol — the protocol-layer between QQ wire bytes and typed events. Owns: identity service (uid↔uin cache with SQLite persistence), event bus, packet pipeline (incoming SSO packet → QQEventVariant), msg-push decoders, element-builder (MessageElement → wire elems[]), highway upload protocol (file/image/video/ptt), OIDB envelope helper, and the event/notice/request type vocabulary. Consumers (@snowluma/core, @snowluma/onebot) talk to this package through `BridgeContext` for runtime calls and the standalone classes (IdentityService, BridgeEventBus, IncomingPacketPipeline) for composition. Per-file subpath exports mirror the legacy `core/src/bridge/*` layout 1:1 so the previous `import { …} from '../bridge/<x>'` collapses to `import { … } from '@snowluma/protocol/<x>'`.",
